        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 5:45AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 545 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of Greenwood, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Garden City and Saint Lawrence.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
